&lt;h1&gt;Staff Nurse - Hindhead Ward&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5:£26,152 - £32,145 per annum, incl HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, committed and hardworking person to join our friendly working environment. Good communication skills and effective interpersonal skills are essential. We are currently working on developing a new Older Persons Unit in our elderly care wards which will give the selected candidates an opportunity to get involved with projects which are aimed at improving care for older persons. Our ward is proud of the Quality Mark awarded to us in providing an Elder Friendly hospital ward. We will ensure that selected candidates do get a detailed induction training which will boost your confidence to work with our patients with complex care needs. Motivated candidates will be supported to enhance their career through advanced training on Dementia care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a tremendous opportunity for service development, and for the post holder to be in a position make a real difference to the older person’s pathway, and experience within the hospital environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are opportunities to develop your confidence and your clinical skills in a supportive environment, to building and extend your existing managerial and clinical knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you require any further information, please contact Senior Sister Laura Taylor on 01483 571122 ext 4692 Or Matron Kirsten Kelly on ext 6870&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
